<br>
 A group of about 12 of us went after him, ranging from 40th to 51th level. It was an all caster raid and out tanks were the pets. We had our highest level mage (51st) lead with an earth pet. One cast from the Kly and the pet was gone. Next cast the mage died. He used 2 Supernovas to accomplish this. Then the Kly rushed us and dropped 2 or 3 Winds of Gelid to finish the rest of us off. The room was about the size of the spell, so it went fast. <br>
<br>
I think we were in shock when our highest went from full to dead in 7.0 seconds and he got the drop on us. I am always motivated to get to 60th level just thinking about the way he tossed us about using these 2 spells. <br>
<br>
I also will give it to Verant by adding more spells to us. I quickly noticed we had less spells than any other class (hybrids not included). Most spells they add now have a use and our spell totals have risen, but not too much crap is being tossed our way. <br>
<br>
Supernova: not that impressive, but brought into the game with just old world gaming. <br>
Winds of Gelid: We can ahcieve a rather impressive amount of mana now Kunark/SoV out so this spell can be useful.<br>
<br>
Muldamai Hearseeker,<br>
56th wizard, Brell Serilis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/13/01 8:07:15 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/sigpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> Supernova and WoG has a blast diameter of 35'. Jyll's and all the other PB's have a blast diameter of 15. In otherwords, as the MoBs start fleeing from the Jyll's attack, you can use Supernova or Winds to finish the fight faster. Or you can open up with it.<br>
<br>
Larger area + More damage = good (in some cases).<br>
Smaller are + Less damage = good (in some cases).<br>
<br>
For instance, say you pull a whole room. 30-35 MoBs. You want to kill them all as fast as you can. If you have multiple Wizards, you can with these spells. Have one or two blast with the large AoEs, and a few to cover the areas around the enchanter(s).<br>
<br>
I've noticed that my PB line-up for the last few fights were:<br>
<br>
Jyll's Static Pulse<br>
Thunderclap<br>
Supernova<br>
<br>
I used Supernova off the bat, then went to Jyll's and then if I needed to move the Mobs, I'd use Thunderclap. Works well if you have a large number of MoBs, and ecomes quite mana efficent.<br>
