<br>
Nobody was debating which type of AoE is more mana effecient. In fact your numbers are dreadfully off. The more targets you have, the harder it becomes to manage their position. Some get caught in the chanters AoE right next to you, some get caught on the outer edge of the AoE stun. More range lets you hit all the MoBs around you, allowing you to not have to worry so much about MoB placement.<br>
<br>
Sure, It's not <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> as mana effecient</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> when you're pulling 10-20 Mobs, but when you've got the right set-up, you can do a hell of alot more damage to a hell of alot more MoBs with less mana.<br>
<br>
I believe the record for PB AoE take-downs is around 35. Thats because the Mobs were stacked tightly. They could have taken down 10 times that amount if they were actually set-up to do it right. It all comes down to placement. If you have only 3 Wizards in a single group, there isn't a reason to try. If you have two groups with 6 Wizards, there is no reason not to try.<br>
